1
00:00:33,828 --> 00:00:35,592
Are we still partners?

2
00:00:37,634 --> 00:00:39,967
We've been business partners
for nearly three years.

3
00:00:40,737 --> 00:00:42,899
This is the first time
we've ever sat together.

4
00:00:43,475 --> 00:00:45,602
We hardly ever see each other.

5
00:00:46,446 --> 00:00:48,914
I know how hard it is for a man
to control his passion.

6
00:00:49,283 --> 00:00:51,774
Partners shouldn't get emotionally
involved with each other.

7
00:04:29,957 --> 00:04:31,618
Fallen Angels

8
00:04:31,659 --> 00:04:32,524
Paging 3662.

9
00:04:32,561 --> 00:04:33,994
I'd like to leave a message.

10
00:04:34,029 --> 00:04:35,463
I'll meet his friends tomorrow.

11
00:04:36,666 --> 00:04:37,860
Where and when?

12
00:04:55,860 --> 00:04:58,386
Most people work from 9 to 5.

13
00:04:58,897 --> 00:05:00,991
I'm the opposite.

14
00:05:01,401 --> 00:05:04,302
My job is simple.

15
00:05:04,338 --> 00:05:07,604
I visit friends now and again.

16
00:05:07,942 --> 00:05:11,071
I don't know any of these people.

17
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:13,511
They don't interest me, either.

18
00:05:13,985 --> 00:05:15,954
Soon, they'll be history.

19
00:07:01,166 --> 00:07:03,567
- Going out?
- Yes.

20
00:07:08,376 --> 00:07:11,541
One's profession is very often
determined by one's personality.

21
00:07:11,814 --> 00:07:14,808
I love my job...
no decision making.

22
00:07:17,424 --> 00:07:21,190
Like who's to die, where and
when - is all planned by others.

23
00:07:22,263 --> 00:07:26,291
I'm a lazy person. I like others
to arrange things for me.

24
00:07:26,669 --> 00:07:28,159
That's why I need a partner.

25
00:10:06,858 --> 00:10:07,883
Ming?

26
00:10:10,096 --> 00:10:11,394
Ming?

27
00:10:12,633 --> 00:10:14,601
It is Ming, isn't it?

28
00:10:14,836 --> 00:10:17,170
Remember me? I'm Hoi.

29
00:10:17,506 --> 00:10:22,003
Remember? We were in the same
class at junior high.

30
00:10:22,314 --> 00:10:23,042
Yes...

31
00:10:23,314 --> 00:10:24,612
What a coincidence

32
00:10:24,649 --> 00:10:27,745
If my Mercedes hadn't broken down
we wouldn't have met.

33
00:10:27,788 --> 00:10:30,188
Everyone has a past.

34
00:10:30,458 --> 00:10:34,293
Even an assassin once had
classmates at junior high.

35
00:10:35,064 --> 00:10:36,930
Whenever I bump into old pals...

36
00:10:37,234 --> 00:10:40,103
...they always ask the
same old questions.

37
00:10:40,772 --> 00:10:43,264
What do you do for a living?

38
00:10:43,709 --> 00:10:46,736
Got a card?
We must keep in touch

39
00:10:47,014 --> 00:10:49,949
Let's arrange something.
What'd you think?

40
00:10:50,253 --> 00:10:52,813
As long as there's money
to make...

41
00:10:54,626 --> 00:10:57,754
You run your own business?

42
00:10:58,096 --> 00:10:59,792
Are you married?

43
00:11:00,099 --> 00:11:02,933
Don't tell me you're still single?

44
00:11:03,303 --> 00:11:07,833
Hey a son.
He looks exactly like you

45
00:11:08,177 --> 00:11:11,671
You're telling me...Your
wife's a nigger, eh?

46
00:11:11,981 --> 00:11:15,077
You're very liberal.
Blacks...They're beautiful.

47
00:11:15,386 --> 00:11:19,825
Color doesn't matter, does it?
You really look like a couple.

48
00:11:20,160 --> 00:11:22,356
Say, are you insured?

49
00:11:22,665 --> 00:11:27,194
Think about it. I'm a pro.
Insurance is my business.

50
00:11:27,470 --> 00:11:30,668
You know, I've been crowned
'King of the Brokers'… 

51
00:11:30,708 --> 00:11:32,232
...in Southeast Asia.

52
00:11:32,511 --> 00:11:36,244
TlME is doing an interview
with me in the next few days.

53
00:11:36,516 --> 00:11:38,951
Look, for old time's sake...

54
00:11:39,221 --> 00:11:42,055
I'll work out a decent plan for you.

55
00:11:42,791 --> 00:11:45,591
You may not want to hear this...

56
00:11:45,896 --> 00:11:49,995
...but accidents happen, your
family needs protection.

57
00:11:50,236 --> 00:11:51,897
Your job involves travel.

58
00:11:51,936 --> 00:11:54,372
You must think of your
family unit.

59
00:11:54,641 --> 00:11:56,701
Would an insurance company...

60
00:11:56,944 --> 00:11:59,210
...underwrite a professional
killer, I wonder?

61
00:11:59,448 --> 00:12:03,750
I'd love to take up his offer...
but who do I name as beneficiary?

62
00:12:04,054 --> 00:12:07,684
Remember the big bosom?
The one we both fancied?

63
00:12:07,727 --> 00:12:10,821
We're getting married next week.
Here's an invitation card.

64
00:12:10,864 --> 00:12:14,926
Just fill in your name, okay?

65
00:12:15,371 --> 00:12:18,671
Please come, and I'll have
the insurance ready for you.

66
00:12:18,708 --> 00:12:21,338
Bring your wife along, too.
See you.

67
00:12:21,912 --> 00:12:26,044
Ages ago I paid a black woman
$30 to pose with me for a photo.

68
00:12:26,387 --> 00:12:29,618
Whenever people asked
I'd say she's my wife.

69
00:12:29,991 --> 00:12:33,985
And the kid in the picture? I think
I bought him an ice cream.

70
00:12:34,429 --> 00:12:37,526
I always wanted to go
to a wedding reception.

71
00:12:38,769 --> 00:12:41,763
But I know it's not my scene.

72
00:14:38,735 --> 00:14:40,601
Sifting through a man's rubbish...

73
00:14:40,972 --> 00:14:44,239
...one can easily find clues
as to his background.

74
00:14:45,313 --> 00:14:48,009
He visits this bar a lot.

75
00:14:51,254 --> 00:14:52,688
Likes the laid-back atmosphere.

76
00:14:53,122 --> 00:14:57,152
I always sit at the same table
he sat at.

77
00:14:57,195 --> 00:15:00,893
Makes me feel sort of
closer to him.

78
00:15:04,639 --> 00:15:10,341
There are some people you
can never get close to.

79
00:15:10,647 --> 00:15:16,053
Get too close,
and you'll find him boring.

80
00:15:16,923 --> 00:15:21,096
I'm someone
who plays by the rules.

81
00:15:21,097 --> 00:15:26,262
I know how to be easygoing.

82
00:20:02,185 --> 00:20:03,881
No, he hasn't come home.

83
00:20:04,189 --> 00:20:08,057
- You're telling the truth?
- Why should I lie?

84
00:20:09,396 --> 00:20:12,161
You live here?

85
00:20:12,868 --> 00:20:14,061
Of course.

86
00:20:14,303 --> 00:20:16,567
- Ever seen this person?
- No.

87
00:20:29,357 --> 00:20:32,953
Keep out of sight.
The cops are still outside.

88
00:20:47,016 --> 00:20:48,107
Where is your son?

89
00:20:48,584 --> 00:20:51,076
We rub shoulders with people
every day.

90
00:20:51,788 --> 00:20:55,691
Strangers who may even become
friends or confidants.

91
00:20:56,227 --> 00:21:00,893
One thing I do know - these cops
will never be my friends.

92
00:21:01,801 --> 00:21:05,638
My name's He Qiwu.
My prison number was 223.

93
00:21:06,609 --> 00:21:09,943
I haven't seen him for days.
I'll inform you when he returns.

94
00:21:10,314 --> 00:21:12,943
I saw him come in.
I want the truth.

95
00:21:17,658 --> 00:21:19,387
That's enough. Keep still.

96
00:21:39,188 --> 00:21:41,019
I'm a very happy man.

97
00:21:41,390 --> 00:21:43,655
I was very talkative
when I was small.

98
00:21:43,994 --> 00:21:48,057
But since eating an out of date can
of pineapple when I was five...

99
00:21:48,367 --> 00:21:50,563
…I lost my voice.

100
00:21:51,471 --> 00:21:54,271
For this reason,
I have very few friends.

101
00:21:54,575 --> 00:21:57,603
I also found it difficult
to find a job.

102
00:21:57,980 --> 00:22:01,440
So I finally decided
to be my own boss.

103
00:22:19,008 --> 00:22:22,071
Having no capital,
my only option...

104
00:22:22,315 --> 00:22:26,582
...was to enter shops after hours
and run my business that way.

105
00:22:26,887 --> 00:22:30,881
I don't mean to take advantage,
but it's practical...

106
00:22:31,594 --> 00:22:34,621
to run an all-night business.

107
00:22:35,197 --> 00:22:41,868
Customers do come in at 3 a.m.
to buy meat. Business is business.

108
00:22:41,909 --> 00:22:44,742
Always satisfy the needs
of your customer.

109
00:22:45,012 --> 00:22:48,711
As the old saying goes,
'The customer is always right'.

110
00:22:49,152 --> 00:22:52,884
And as the boss, I must be
kind, caring and tolerant.

111
00:22:52,924 --> 00:22:55,188
One can't afford to be selfish...

112
00:22:55,227 --> 00:22:58,425
...there's no such thing as a
free lunch in this world.

113
00:22:58,465 --> 00:23:02,095
I always work very hard at night
- well, until very late.

114
00:23:02,435 --> 00:23:06,100
I don't make a fortune,
but I'm happy.

115
00:23:23,732 --> 00:23:26,897
Are you crazy? Why are you
making me wash my clothes?

116
00:23:26,938 --> 00:23:30,432
I'm a beggar. The last thing
I need is a laundry.

117
00:23:30,474 --> 00:23:32,238
Leave me alone...

118
00:23:33,747 --> 00:23:37,741
You are crazy.
Get your hands off my clothes.

119
00:23:38,019 --> 00:23:42,479
Sod off!
I'll smash you to pulp.

120
00:23:42,792 --> 00:23:46,561
Okay, I'll pay you...
if it's money you want.

121
00:23:47,132 --> 00:23:48,223
Cretin

122
00:23:50,637 --> 00:23:53,629
Leave it
I don't want an eggplant.

123
00:23:53,908 --> 00:23:57,437
No, I don't want them
I must act like a lady.

124
00:23:57,713 --> 00:24:00,878
I don't accept freebies from
strangers. People will talk.

125
00:24:01,185 --> 00:24:03,347
I'll have a melon, okay?

126
00:24:05,524 --> 00:24:06,354
Here!

127
00:24:12,367 --> 00:24:15,565
What the hell
You crazy or something?

128
00:24:16,138 --> 00:24:17,801
Stop that

129
00:24:19,944 --> 00:24:24,279
Listen, I washed
my hair yesterday...

130
00:24:28,189 --> 00:24:32,217
Ouch, take it easy...

131
00:24:32,562 --> 00:24:34,928
Don't scratch

132
00:24:38,304 --> 00:24:40,864
I just want a late snack.

133
00:24:41,074 --> 00:24:43,008
I don't need a shampoo.

134
00:24:46,948 --> 00:24:49,746
Okay, you win.
Do what you like

135
00:24:54,926 --> 00:24:55,950
No.

136
00:24:56,929 --> 00:24:59,764
I don't want a shave

137
00:25:06,576 --> 00:25:08,272
Don't touch me...

138
00:25:13,117 --> 00:25:15,781
Listen, I know I'm difficult,
but I know some...

139
00:25:16,956 --> 00:25:18,015
...who aren't

140
00:25:21,229 --> 00:25:24,860
Please don't shave me...
I don't want a shave...

141
00:25:25,136 --> 00:25:27,400
I'll pay you not to, okay?

142
00:25:28,772 --> 00:25:30,070
Thanks.

143
00:25:31,144 --> 00:25:33,339
A double cone, please.

144
00:25:35,415 --> 00:25:36,907
Fuck, it's you.

145
00:25:37,219 --> 00:25:39,745
I'm sorry...sorry...

146
00:25:48,701 --> 00:25:51,865
Stop pulling my hair, okay?

147
00:25:51,904 --> 00:25:54,466
I'll serve myself.

148
00:26:02,286 --> 00:26:03,515
I'll do it.

149
00:26:10,864 --> 00:26:14,597
Hi, it's me.
What are you doing?

150
00:26:16,907 --> 00:26:18,933
Go to bed, don't wait up.

151
00:26:21,547 --> 00:26:24,210
I'm having some ice cream.

152
00:26:25,018 --> 00:26:28,716
I hope I can come home soon.dd

153
00:26:29,157 --> 00:26:32,685
I don't know how much more
I'll have to eat.

154
00:26:33,329 --> 00:26:35,925
Of course I'll have to pay

155
00:26:41,041 --> 00:26:44,239
Look, I've run into this guy, and...

156
00:26:44,811 --> 00:26:47,281
What's to explain?
It's the truth

157
00:26:49,320 --> 00:26:51,915
Come down and see for yourself.

158
00:26:52,189 --> 00:26:53,986
Hey

159
00:26:58,431 --> 00:27:02,267
Oh, no way
I can't eat that.

160
00:27:04,740 --> 00:27:06,606
It'll burn my mustache.

161
00:27:08,378 --> 00:27:10,142
This is beyond a joke...

162
00:27:14,621 --> 00:27:17,649
What the hell's going on?

163
00:27:17,892 --> 00:27:21,954
I said come by yourself. I didn't
say bring dad and the kids

164
00:27:22,397 --> 00:27:25,367
Too much ice cream's
bad for dad.

165
00:27:25,601 --> 00:27:27,968
What if something happens?

166
00:27:29,008 --> 00:27:31,773
And the kids have school tomorrow.

167
00:27:32,112 --> 00:27:34,012
What's that...?

168
00:27:39,187 --> 00:27:44,786
I don't want to die
from eating too much ice cream.

169
00:27:44,962 --> 00:27:47,261
Look, I'm being serious.

170
00:27:48,534 --> 00:27:50,934
I'll pay you, okay?

171
00:27:51,238 --> 00:27:55,403
Tell me how much, and I'll
buy all the ice cream. Go on.

172
00:27:58,448 --> 00:28:00,917
My ice cream may be a
bit more expensive...

173
00:28:01,485 --> 00:28:04,579
...but I think this family's
having a great time tonight.

174
00:28:06,025 --> 00:28:09,894
I love ice cream.
When I was a kid...

175
00:28:09,930 --> 00:28:12,923
...an ice cream van always
stopped outside our place.

176
00:28:12,968 --> 00:28:15,130
Every time I saw it
I was happy.

177
00:28:16,106 --> 00:28:20,407
I even asked my dad why he
didn't drive an ice cream van.

178
00:28:21,012 --> 00:28:24,141
He didn't answer me.
I later found out...

179
00:28:24,517 --> 00:28:27,749
...that my mum was killed
by an ice cream van.

180
00:28:29,992 --> 00:28:31,824
I was born in Taiwan...

181
00:28:31,860 --> 00:28:35,060
...and came to Hong Kong
with dad when I was five.

182
00:28:35,099 --> 00:28:37,898
He worked as an assistant
in Chungking Mansions.

183
00:28:38,204 --> 00:28:42,472
After my mum's death
he very rarely talked.

184
00:28:42,509 --> 00:28:44,704
And we never ate ice cream.

185
00:28:46,381 --> 00:28:49,216
The fact that we're both
quiet and subtle...

186
00:28:49,251 --> 00:28:51,846
...probably explains the
close bond between us.

187
00:28:54,760 --> 00:28:59,131
What are you thinking of?

188
00:28:59,833 --> 00:29:02,166
And why the ice cream?

189
00:29:18,426 --> 00:29:21,920
You know I don't like ice cream.
It's too cold...

190
00:29:22,331 --> 00:29:24,926
...and it gives me the runs.

191
00:29:38,354 --> 00:29:39,684
You're crazy

192
00:29:54,576 --> 00:29:58,378
Let me out!
What are you playing at?

193
00:30:01,419 --> 00:30:05,323
What are you doing?
I'll kill you!

194
00:30:05,657 --> 00:30:08,183
Open this door!
You hear?

195
00:30:22,448 --> 00:30:24,440
Paging 9090.

196
00:30:24,852 --> 00:30:27,481
I'd like to leave a message.

197
00:30:27,755 --> 00:30:30,316
I'll meet his friends tomorrow.

198
00:30:31,026 --> 00:30:33,723
Let me know where and when.

199
00:32:16,640 --> 00:32:19,838
It's crystal clear...crystal clear...

200
00:32:20,946 --> 00:32:25,180
I just want to check
that I've got the right place.

201
00:32:25,420 --> 00:32:28,446
It's a fast-food place,
not a barber shop.

202
00:32:28,690 --> 00:32:32,423
You may think that we're
making a lot of money.

203
00:32:33,397 --> 00:32:36,094
What price is a human life?

204
00:32:36,367 --> 00:32:37,766
Depends on your luck.

205
00:32:37,970 --> 00:32:39,563
Business can be slack for ages.

206
00:32:39,839 --> 00:32:41,900
So, to make a living...

207
00:32:42,142 --> 00:32:44,167
…I'll occasionally invest
in other businesses.

208
00:32:44,212 --> 00:32:46,578
Like debt collection.

209
00:32:46,615 --> 00:32:47,707
Thanks.

210
00:32:51,622 --> 00:32:52,782
Hold on. I'll get your money.

211
00:32:58,531 --> 00:32:59,226
Here.

212
00:34:37,736 --> 00:34:40,000
But lately. I've suffered
quite a few injuries.

213
00:34:40,974 --> 00:34:44,104
I hate digging bullets
out of my own body.

214
00:34:45,146 --> 00:34:47,082
It's very exhausting.

215
00:34:50,052 --> 00:34:51,715
I went to bed early that night.

216
00:34:52,892 --> 00:34:55,952
When I awoke next morning,
I came to a decision.

217
00:35:10,649 --> 00:35:12,776
Lady, we're closed.

218
00:35:13,719 --> 00:35:16,347
Two weeks after I was
injured, I asked her out.

219
00:35:17,325 --> 00:35:19,019
I wanted to tell her my decision.

220
00:35:20,328 --> 00:35:24,097
But...I didn't show up.

221
00:35:46,899 --> 00:35:51,396
I'm sure she'll come looking
for me in a couple of days.

222
00:35:52,772 --> 00:35:56,473
After all, we've been partners
for a long time.

223
00:36:03,589 --> 00:36:07,823
Being partners, you get to
understand each other.

224
00:36:08,529 --> 00:36:09,962
Almost able to read
each other's minds.

225
00:36:09,997 --> 00:36:11,967
I'd often leave her some clues...

226
00:36:13,703 --> 00:36:16,265
...to trace my actions, or
my whereabouts.

227
00:36:17,474 --> 00:36:19,876
After all these years,
she's become part of my life.

228
00:36:26,887 --> 00:36:28,981
But nothing can remain
the same forever.

229
00:36:29,892 --> 00:36:32,589
I have to tell her
that I desperately want out.

230
00:36:33,197 --> 00:36:36,828
But I don't know how to start.

231
00:36:38,805 --> 00:36:41,272
So, I've devised another method.

232
00:36:47,650 --> 00:36:49,983
A woman may come in
asking for me.

233
00:36:50,254 --> 00:36:51,744
Please give her this coin...

234
00:36:52,023 --> 00:36:54,514
...and tell her that 1818
is my lucky number.

235
00:37:07,412 --> 00:37:11,439
1818...it's the code for one of
the songs in this jukebox.

236
00:37:12,452 --> 00:37:14,352
After she's listened to the song...

237
00:37:14,620 --> 00:37:16,350
she'll understand my message.

238
00:38:27,356 --> 00:38:28,322
Okay if I sit here?

239
00:38:58,800 --> 00:39:01,200
It's raining

240
00:39:03,739 --> 00:39:07,404
Let's have some fun
Oh, it feels so great

241
00:39:07,811 --> 00:39:09,474
Come on

242
00:39:28,608 --> 00:39:29,301
Why?

243
00:39:29,775 --> 00:39:32,370
Perhaps I'm tense...

244
00:39:32,914 --> 00:39:33,779
Why?

245
00:39:34,983 --> 00:39:36,142
You coming?

246
00:39:37,352 --> 00:39:38,284
No?

247
00:39:40,357 --> 00:39:41,550
Okay

248
00:39:46,299 --> 00:39:48,268
Sure you don't want to come?

249
00:39:48,569 --> 00:39:50,332
Made up your mind?

250
00:39:51,272 --> 00:39:52,399
Forget it

251
00:39:58,248 --> 00:40:01,378
Hey...come and get it

252
00:40:13,337 --> 00:40:16,433
It's not drying.

253
00:40:18,475 --> 00:40:21,470
I'll take it to the cleaners
for you tomorrow.

254
00:40:21,948 --> 00:40:23,142
Okay?

255
00:40:25,720 --> 00:40:28,053
