01:10:53,227 --> 01:10:56,026
…I caught dad having a
sneak look at the tape.

522
01:10:56,497 --> 01:10:58,261
He really enjoyed it.

523
01:10:59,235 --> 01:11:01,534
My memory's not that good.
but...

524
01:11:02,239 --> 01:11:06,576
…I did remember that it was
his 60th birthday.

525
01:11:07,779 --> 01:11:11,980
God knows why. But he gets
great amusement watching it.

526
01:11:12,288 --> 01:11:14,552
And I do know that he's happy.

527
01:11:16,659 --> 01:11:18,424
Silly devil...

528
01:11:42,229 --> 01:11:44,629
Working with someone
for a long time...

529
01:11:44,865 --> 01:11:47,595
...you're bound to be influenced
in some way.

530
01:11:47,868 --> 01:11:49,804
I know that fragrance...

531
01:11:51,508 --> 01:11:54,603
...but I'm not used to smelling
it on other women.

532
01:12:01,856 --> 01:12:04,347
This suits me just fine.

533
01:12:04,959 --> 01:12:07,725
It's shrunk a bit, though.

534
01:12:12,604 --> 01:12:15,903
I always thought the perfume
was a bit overpowering.

535
01:12:17,111 --> 01:12:20,605
I smelt it on this other woman
this afternoon.

536
01:12:21,583 --> 01:12:23,711
She wants to see you.

537
01:12:24,087 --> 01:12:26,112
I fixed up a meeting.

538
01:12:27,758 --> 01:12:28,817
Will you go?

539
01:12:34,000 --> 01:12:37,597
I think you should go and
get things sorted out.

540
01:12:41,044 --> 01:12:43,309
Perhaps it's not such a good idea.

541
01:12:49,955 --> 01:12:52,117
Anyway, I thought you'd go.

542
01:12:53,728 --> 01:12:54,956
This is for you.

543
01:13:48,838 --> 01:13:50,396
I'd like...

544
01:13:51,509 --> 01:13:53,067
...a packet of crisps.

545
01:13:53,744 --> 01:13:56,213
Not the red pack, the yellow

546
01:14:33,700 --> 01:14:36,168
They sit there together
for ages.

547
01:14:36,737 --> 01:14:38,729
I wonder what they're talking about?

548
01:14:39,174 --> 01:14:42,509
Meanwhile the rain keeps
bucketing down.

549
01:14:42,847 --> 01:14:46,784
It's raining so heavily, how will
I get home by myself?

550
01:15:03,008 --> 01:15:05,636
And just when I need
a raincoat...

551
01:15:06,513 --> 01:15:08,573
...he appears at my side.

552
01:15:11,721 --> 01:15:13,551
I hope the rain...

553
01:15:14,958 --> 01:15:16,219
...will never stop.

554
01:15:21,100 --> 01:15:23,193
I'm not coming in.

555
01:15:23,802 --> 01:15:29,300
Then why walk me home?

556
01:15:31,281 --> 01:15:34,046
You could've let me walk

557
01:15:34,317 --> 01:15:36,377
I was going to do that anyway.

558
01:15:36,687 --> 01:15:39,486
You trying to be funny?

559
01:15:40,459 --> 01:15:43,953
Oh, what the hell.
Just fuck off, will you?

560
01:15:47,970 --> 01:15:49,528
We came to an agreement.

561
01:15:49,806 --> 01:15:51,638
I never agreed to anything.

562
01:15:52,275 --> 01:15:55,838
You insisted on seeing her, not me.
What'd you want from me now?

563
01:15:57,684 --> 01:16:01,416
You think I'm stupid?
Oh, get lost.

564
01:16:04,560 --> 01:16:07,290
You're a cheat and a liar.

565
01:16:12,336 --> 01:16:14,569
Give me your hand...

566
01:16:20,582 --> 01:16:24,075
Why?

567
01:16:24,354 --> 01:16:26,586
I've left my mark, okay?

568
01:16:27,157 --> 01:16:30,890
You may forget my face, but
you won't forget my bite.

569
01:16:34,101 --> 01:16:36,730
I'm easily recognized, though...

570
01:16:37,038 --> 01:16:40,702
...by the mole on my face.

571
01:16:40,977 --> 01:16:44,675
If a woman with a mole on her
face ever comes up to you...

572
01:16:46,118 --> 01:16:48,781
...it could be me.

573
01:16:52,292 --> 01:16:54,659
Will you remember that?

574
01:16:58,434 --> 01:17:00,164
I'll remember.

575
01:17:27,076 --> 01:17:29,168
Will I remember her?

576
01:17:30,979 --> 01:17:33,074
Actually, it's not important.

577
01:17:33,383 --> 01:17:38,322
For her I was an oasis in
her journey through life.

578
01:17:38,590 --> 01:17:40,718
I hope she soon reaches
her destination...

579
01:17:40,993 --> 01:17:43,656
...and finds her soulmate
for life.

580
01:17:43,932 --> 01:17:45,866
We all need a partner.

581
01:17:47,635 --> 01:17:49,867
When will I find mine?

582
01:17:58,118 --> 01:18:00,716
Are we still partners?

583
01:18:19,179 --> 01:18:23,620
I don't know how to answer
her question.

584
01:18:23,920 --> 01:18:27,617
I've come to look at partners
from a new angle.

585
01:18:28,759 --> 01:18:30,854
As a business partner,
she's perfect...

586
01:18:31,197 --> 01:18:35,659
...but not one you could
spend your life with.

587
01:18:38,040 --> 01:18:40,771
I'm terminating
our business relationship.

588
01:18:53,762 --> 01:18:57,492
Do me one last favor, will you?

589
01:19:06,210 --> 01:19:09,789
I don't know why I agreed.

590
01:19:10,646 --> 01:19:13,142
Probably because it's a last favor.

591
01:19:35,219 --> 01:19:37,051
I want to place an advert
for my friend.

592
01:19:41,661 --> 01:19:43,459
I want the front page.

593
01:23:10,718 --> 01:23:15,954
The best thing about my job -
I don't have to make decisions.

594
01:23:16,795 --> 01:23:22,531
Who's to die, when and where,
it's all been planned by others.

595
01:23:25,674 --> 01:23:27,231
I'm a lazy person.

596
01:23:28,444 --> 01:23:30,912
I like others to arrange things for me.

597
01:23:32,548 --> 01:23:34,949
But I've been doing some
thinking lately.

598
01:23:35,353 --> 01:23:37,822
I feel the need for change.

599
01:23:38,992 --> 01:23:41,017
Whether it's right or wrong...

600
01:23:41,929 --> 01:23:45,366
…I must make a decision
for myself.

601
01:24:28,593 --> 01:24:30,459
'Being photographed will
shorten your life'.

602
01:24:31,531 --> 01:24:33,591
Seems there's some truth in it.

603
01:24:34,735 --> 01:24:36,795
One evening,
dad was taken ill.

604
01:24:37,640 --> 01:24:39,301
I took him to hospital.

605
01:24:41,078 --> 01:24:43,808
A little later, he passed away.

606
01:24:46,484 --> 01:24:48,043
Thanks to him, all my life...

607
01:24:48,087 --> 01:24:50,956
…I've always felt like
a little boy.

608
01:24:52,393 --> 01:24:55,523
He was always there to
sort out my problems.

609
01:24:57,200 --> 01:25:00,067
Packing his things away
that evening...

610
01:25:00,104 --> 01:25:05,059
He was always there to
sort out my problems.

611
01:25:07,281 --> 01:25:11,211
Packing his things away
that evening...

612
01:25:12,111 --> 01:25:15,040
…I felt grown-up for the first time.

613
01:25:28,579 --> 01:25:31,313
I didn't want to be grown-up...
…I just wanted dad with me.

614
01:25:31,347 --> 01:25:33,976
When I left the hotel...

615
01:25:34,318 --> 01:25:35,217
…I took the videotapes with me.

616
01:25:35,454 --> 01:25:36,784
I watched them
over and over again.

617
01:27:22,167 --> 01:27:25,138
Watching dad cooking
made me very happy.

618
01:27:26,641 --> 01:27:30,602
I know I'll never taste
his steaks again...

619
01:27:31,147 --> 01:27:34,481
...but I'll never forget
just how they tasted.

620
01:27:40,793 --> 01:27:43,593
Oh, hell, it's you again.

621
01:27:43,865 --> 01:27:45,561
Not the hair. Leave it...

622
01:27:46,835 --> 01:27:50,203
I'm happy to be your client.

623
01:27:50,675 --> 01:27:52,540
Did I ever refuse?

624
01:27:53,011 --> 01:27:55,036
I didn't, did I?

625
01:27:55,314 --> 01:27:58,079
Just look at me
Let go of me...

626
01:27:58,319 --> 01:28:00,311
My wife's visiting China...

627
01:28:00,588 --> 01:28:03,582
...and I've some business
to attend to.

628
01:28:03,925 --> 01:28:06,555
Give me three hours and
I'll be back.

629
01:28:06,797 --> 01:28:09,529
Three hours, okay?
Three hours...

630
01:28:10,936 --> 01:28:12,596
Two hours?

631
01:28:12,840 --> 01:28:15,205
Two hours and I'll be back. Deal?

632
01:28:16,310 --> 01:28:20,838
Trust me. We're old friends,
aren't we?

633
01:28:20,882 --> 01:28:24,445
People cross all the time.
Two hours...

634
01:28:24,756 --> 01:28:28,817
Trust me, you have my word.
We're like brothers, right?

635
01:28:30,864 --> 01:28:33,231
You want it written in blood?

636
01:28:33,501 --> 01:28:35,766
You're kidding, right?

637
01:28:36,170 --> 01:28:38,470
Leave it out...

638
01:28:38,742 --> 01:28:41,837
Just one hour, okay?

639
01:28:42,112 --> 01:28:45,743
Don't do this...
have mercy... Wait...

640
01:28:48,688 --> 01:28:51,386
Can I have some
small change, please?

641
01:28:58,269 --> 01:28:59,257
Thanks.

642
01:29:03,777 --> 01:29:06,406
I'm downstairs already.

643
01:29:06,746 --> 01:29:09,409
I'm waiting for you. 'Bye.

644
01:29:18,497 --> 01:29:21,092
Talk about bad timing...

645
01:29:21,500 --> 01:29:25,666
Shortly after dad died,
Sato-san returned to Japan.

646
01:29:26,708 --> 01:29:29,109
I haven't got much money saved...

647
01:29:29,145 --> 01:29:32,582
...so I can only do what I'm
best at - being my own boss.

648
01:29:33,249 --> 01:29:35,913
I'm being very cautious this time.

649
01:29:35,954 --> 01:29:38,549
I pick only the stronger ones.

650
01:29:38,591 --> 01:29:41,221
Ones that won't get hurt easily.

651
01:29:41,529 --> 01:29:44,589
Take this one for example.
Guts of steel.

652
01:29:44,867 --> 01:29:46,835
Saves a lot of hassle.

653
01:29:47,370 --> 01:29:50,498
Sometimes I run into
old acquaintances.

654
01:29:50,541 --> 01:29:53,204
Some haven't changed at all.

655
01:29:53,512 --> 01:29:56,038
Others I hardly recognize.

656
01:29:56,549 --> 01:29:58,983
I'm always glad to see them...

657
01:29:59,321 --> 01:30:02,484
...even though they may not
remember me.

658
01:30:03,826 --> 01:30:07,787
Of course, there are some
exceptions to the rule.

659
01:30:08,098 --> 01:30:10,761
On August 29th, 1995...

660
01:30:11,035 --> 01:30:13,939
…I ran into my first love again.

661
01:30:13,974 --> 01:30:16,204
I don't think she recognized me.

662
01:30:18,312 --> 01:30:20,804
I guess I'm more handsome now.

663
01:30:29,162 --> 01:30:31,597
- You're late.
- Sorry.

664
01:30:31,899 --> 01:30:35,358
- What's up with him?
- I've no idea.

665
01:30:51,960 --> 01:30:54,930
It turned quite cold that evening.

666
01:30:55,932 --> 01:30:59,461
I hadn't expected winter
to come so soon.

667
01:31:05,813 --> 01:31:08,214
I'm not used to this
kind of weather.

668
01:31:09,618 --> 01:31:13,181
It seems to have been
a long winter.

669
01:31:14,058 --> 01:31:17,222
Although I eat well every day...

670
01:31:18,095 --> 01:31:20,258
…I still feel cold.

671
01:31:21,000 --> 01:31:24,564
I've got used to working alone.

672
01:31:26,241 --> 01:31:30,839
Occasionally I do work
with others...

673
01:31:30,881 --> 01:31:34,318
...but not on a regular basis.

674
01:31:35,420 --> 01:31:38,185
I've learnt to be more careful.

675
01:31:39,359 --> 01:31:43,695
For instance, I won't work
in hotels any more.

676
01:31:44,266 --> 01:31:47,362
And no more checking out
rubbish bins.

677
01:31:48,138 --> 01:31:50,630
I firmly believe...

678
01:31:50,942 --> 01:31:54,880
...one mustn't get emotionally
involved with one's partner.

679
01:32:52,661 --> 01:32:55,256
We rub shoulders with many
people every day.

680
01:32:56,165 --> 01:32:59,864
Some may become close friends,
or confidants.

681
01:33:00,304 --> 01:33:03,367
That's why I'm always optimistic.

682
01:33:04,711 --> 01:33:06,804
Sometimes it hurts.

683
01:33:07,215 --> 01:33:10,015
Not to worry -
I try to stay happy.

684
01:33:15,160 --> 01:33:18,755
That night,
I saw that woman again.

685
01:33:19,031 --> 01:33:22,002
I knew we'd never be friends
or confidants...

686
01:33:22,235 --> 01:33:25,638
...we'd let too many chances
pass us by.

687
01:33:25,940 --> 01:33:29,810
Nothing happened,
there was no chemistry.

688
01:33:30,213 --> 01:33:32,648
Maybe it was the weather...

689
01:33:32,984 --> 01:33:36,545
...but that night
I found her very alluring.

690
01:34:12,872 --> 01:34:17,607
I'm about to leave,
I ask him to take me home.

691
01:34:18,147 --> 01:34:21,584
I haven't ridden pillion
for a long time...

692
01:34:21,917 --> 01:34:25,515
...nor have I been this close
to a man in ages.

693
01:34:26,558 --> 01:34:30,017
The road home isn't very long...

694
01:34:30,898 --> 01:34:34,766
...and I know I'll be
getting off soon.

695
01:34:34,803 --> 01:34:37,329
But at this moment, I'm feeling
such lovely warmth.
